\begin_layout Plain Layout

[(c)]
\end_layout

\end_inset

There are 
\begin_inset Formula $6^{6}$
\end_inset

 ordered draws of 6 numbers from 6 numbers with replacement.
 There are 
\begin_inset Formula $6!$
\end_inset

 different arrangements of 
\begin_inset Formula $\{2,7,7,8,14,14\}$
\end_inset

 but there is overcounting by 
\begin_inset Formula $2!2!$
\end_inset

.
 So there are 
\begin_inset Formula $6!/2!2!$
\end_inset

 different ordered draws that correspond to the unordered draw of 
\begin_inset Formula $\{2,7,7,8,14,14\}$
\end_inset

.
 So the probability is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{6!/2!2!}{6^{6}}=\frac{6!/4}{6^{6}}=
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset ERT
